Week 7 - Lab 6

Shellcode Writing

Introduction

In this lab the students should write and test a shellcode. The students should
develop from scratch the shellcode for the exit system call.

* Step 1

See how exit works in C.

* Step 2

Write the shellcode in asm:

.section .data
.section .text
.globl _start
 
_start:
    xor  %eax, %eax
    inc  %eax
    mov  %eax, %ebx
    int  $0x80

$ as --32 exit-sh.s -o exit-sh.o
$ ld -m elf_i386 exit-sh.o -o exit-sh
$ ./exit-sh
$ 

